			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">/agree except I found sending the pet in would aggro one bloodgill onto my pet and the other would make a beeline straight to me, getting a few free hits on me before I could get close enough to my pet for it to 'peel' (using /pet back off, /pet attack hotkey) the goblin off me, slowing down the entire killing process (and making it a little dangerous)
<br />

<br />
I think this is from the pet aggro changes from a while back, both gobbies will not engage on your pet as soon as it enters aggro range, but will wait until the pet actually attacked before aggro, thus leaving some separation between the goblins.
<br />

<br />
My slightly modified tactics are (4 successful levels, died only once when I clicked off enduring breath instead of eye of zomm by mistake <img src="images/smiles/icon_rolleyes.gif" alt="Rolling Eyes" border="0" /> 
<br />
)....
<br />

<br />
(a) 44+ I use a fully armored (summon plate, weapons, back, neck, rings) fire pet, so I don't have to use mana on a damage shield.
<br />

<br />
(b) Use an Eye of Zomm (Clay bracelet is a plus here) to scout the corners to target the bloodgills. This lets you target them from close to maximum casting distance.
<br />

<br />
(c) use my white ceramic band to cast a 5 pt. damage spell on one of the goblins from max. distance. 
<br />

<br />
(d) count to two, send it pet at the onrushing goblins, 95% of the time I get both on the pet this way, if not, my pet is really closeby to 'peel' the second off me.
<br />

<br />
(e) heal pet once (if required), /assist pet to target the bloodgill it is fighting and cast blaze when it is at half health or less. First goblin dies
<br />

<br />
(f) either use ceramic band (if pet is still healthy) or blaze (if pet is lower in health) to finish off the second goblin.
<br />

<br />
Clearing all 12 spawnpoints before they respawn will net you 25-30% exp. per hour, which is fantastic in the mid-late 40s. This camp is doable at 39, but I think the Tundra Yetis/Western Dreadlands are faster until 44. At 49, these are too simple, with diminishing exp. returns, and after dinging 52, it will be time to wave goodbye to the bloodgills and find a new hunting spot (If you haven't already).
<br />

<br />
see also <a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/tower/viewtopic.php?t=3520" target="_blank">http://forum.magecompendium.com/tower/viewtopic.php?t=3520</a>
<br />
and <a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/tower/viewtopic.php?t=630" target="_blank">http://forum.magecompendium.com/tower/viewtopic.php?t=630</a><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=392942" target="_blank" class="postlink">Wicc Vanwinkle</a>
