				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I can highly recommend Bloodgills -- the "best" XP spot I know of. The Bloodgills 101 posting referenced above was my starting point and I levelled from 44 through hitting 50 (51??) there.
<br />

<br />
Bring a fishing pole and lots of bait! Remember to train one point before heading out. Fishing 1-130s out there. Too bad you can't fish underwater...
<br />

<br />
Swimming maxed *again* -- good thing, you *will* need 200 swimming in other places.
<br />

<br />
Turn off /ooc and /shout
<br />

<br />
Find your own technique -- I tried several. It changed from level to level with spells. Watch your aggro -- as the previous poster mentioned, if you nuke too early, or sit too quickly, the second will aggro on you. /assist your pet before nuking.
<br />

<br />
Use /pet sit to mark the "runners" -- I was making about 100 pp an hour on drops *and* XP!!
<br />

<br />
Watch in awe as your 49 Fire RIPS through things -- bring the spell with you when you think you are going to ding. Tag the pair of them with that low-level rain and rake in the XP.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
