			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">THIS SPOT HAS PROBLEMS
<br />

<br />
I went to the Bloodgill goblin camp at level 46.  At level 46 each goblin is between 0.75% and 1.2% XP, not bad, although there are better XP spots at this level (solb is one).  It is a great place to get swimming skill up while getting decent XP, but are a couple of problems.  
<br />

<br />
One, certain areas of the camp have very serious pet pathing problems.  Several times when I told me pet to attack it ran around in circles seemingly unable to find the mob which was right in front of us.  This is even more dangerous when you are being hit and the pet can't peal the mob off because he can't seem to reach you although only a couple feet away.  I died several times that way.  Sometimes summoning the pet works, however if the pathing problems begin when a pet is chasing a runner, summon will not work (can't summon when pet is on mob aggro list).  At that point its best to destroy pet and resummon right away.  Try to keep your pet on the same z axis (depth) as your mage.
<br />

<br />
Two, I find that when fighting in water spells are much more easily inturrupted when a mob is beating on you.  If things go bad, do not expect you can gate out, it is close to impossible to regain concentration in the water (with lev on or off).</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
