			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I leveled from 42 to 50 here.  I leveled every playing session {2-4 hours}.  
<br />

<br />
Here is my method.  At 39th level, use a fully equipped air pet.  {This was before the 500hp + 50 hp weapons from PoP.  With those, the Fire pet may be viable}  At 44th level, use a fully equiped fire pet. 
<br />

<br />
The key is to break the spawns.  On the base of the upper dome is 4 cornes with 2 spawns each.  At the entrance to the Vekstor{SP} there is two guarding the hole and possilbly the maraduer and two posts with singles.  All of the goblins are on a 15 minute spawn except the maraduer which is a much longer spawn time. 
<br />

<br />
I start with two goblins on the base.   I alternate heals and nukes until I kill one.  Then I prolong the next fight by just healing.  If less than 44th, I wait till 2 minutes after first one dies before I kill the second one.  44th and above I only wait one minute.  You may have to back off your pet and follow it a bit, but is really important to spilt the spawns.  
<br />

<br />
Once these two are both dead and I have at least 50% mana left, I swim to the next spawn spot and spilt these two as well.  It takes a lot more mana to fight two at once becasue of the healing needed to keep the pet alive.  So once I have cleared the 4 spawns at two different spots, I swim back to the original and sit and wait for them to repop.  Most of the time I get back to full mana and the pet totally reheals.  
<br />

<br />
While sitting there, I see a goblin pop solo {That is why you wait at least 1-2 minutes to kill the second one after the first one dies}.  Pull this goblin with a debuff and swin until you can't see the spawn point.  Now you can kill this goblin at your own pace without worrying about aggroing a second one.  Fighting just one goblin, you don't need to heal you pet and can nuke more/faster.  A minute after this one dies, I attack the other spawn at its spawn point.  I then swim to the next spawn point.   If I have timed it right, I get there before they spawn.  I then spilt these as well per the first spawn.  Since I was only fighting one at a time, I am not using nealy as much mana.  If I have over 50% mana, I break the third spawn point.
<br />

<br />
By spiliting the spawns, you end up fighting only one goblin at a time.  With the timing of the spawns, your pet can heal and you can regen your mana to cover one fight while waiting for the next ones to spawn.  
<br />

<br />
Below 44th, I really needed a KEI to hold the upper 4 spawn points.  I could break all 8 but eventually, I would fall behind and lose my broken spawn.  Since you can't get KEI now, I would probably only do 6 in a cycle and then pick up one of the single spawns from below when I had lots of mana.  
<br />

<br />
At 44th with a KEI, I could talk all the spawn points,  I started with entrance because if the marduer spawn, I needed to be full mana to handle him.  Without KEI, I just attacked the upper eight and added one or two of the single spawns in as mana permiteed. 
<br />

<br />
Good luck!   <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" /><br />_________________<br />Dabrighter Blazemeister
<br />
